OL,3,CWatch as bear rescued from tree after
OL,4,Cwandering into residential street
OL,6,FThe black bear likely wandered into
OL,7,Fthe neighbourhood looking for food
OL,8,Fbefore he went up a tree
OL,10,FA black bear that had wandered onto a
OL,11,Fresidential street in New York, was
OL,12,Fsuccessfully tranquilised and rescued
OL,13,Ffrom a tree on Tuesday.
OL,15,FBlack bears tend to avoid humans but
OL,16,Fcan be dangerous, so local officials
OL,17,Fwere called to the street in Albany to
OL,18,Ftake him back to his natural habitat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/3
